            <p class="text-terminal-red font-semibold mb-2">RALPH Autonomous Loop</p>
            <div class="bg-black p-3 rounded font-mono text-sm overflow-x-auto">
              <p class="text-terminal-green">$ /ralph-loop "Build a REST API for todos.</p>
              <p class="text-terminal-green">  Requirements: CRUD operations, input validation, tests.</p>
              <p class="text-terminal-green">  Output &lt;promise&gt;COMPLETE&lt;/promise&gt; when done."</p>
              <p class="text-terminal-muted">  --completion-promise "COMPLETE"</p>
              <p class="text-terminal-muted">  --max-iterations 50</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-3 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="text-terminal-green font-bold">Result:</span>
              <span class="text-terminal-text">Fully autonomous development - Claude iterates until tests pass and code ships.</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-terminal-bg p-4 rounded-lg border border-terminal-border mt-4">
            <p class="text-terminal-yellow font-semibold mb-2">The Pattern:</p>
            <p class="text-terminal-muted">
              Be specific about outcomes. Let Claude handle implementation. Verify it worked. Iterate.
              These prompts work because they describe <span class="text-terminal-accent">what success looks like</span>, not how to get there.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

